      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0649P0-01156'>
        <a name='S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_202'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-jeff-rooker' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_202' title='Link to this speech by Mr Jeff Rooker' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-jeff-rooker" title="Mr Jeff Rooker">Lord Rooker</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Okay. There are 8,000 parish councils, all varying enormously in size. We are in a different league altogether here. It would not be relevant. They are not covered by the 1988 Act, so the mechanism in the Act could not be used. However, the absence of a special report does not mean that Parliament would no longer be able to consider the grants under Clause 36. Parliamentary approval will still be needed within the ambit of the relevant department's request for resources, and Treasury consent will also be needed.</p><p>
            The grants made under Clause 36 are likely to be quite small or to be repeated. The need to continue to rely on the grant-making powers under Section 88 would be very cumbersome, as I have explained. Therefore, I hope that the amendment will be withdrawn.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-01157'>
