        Clause 37 [<span class="italic">Best value grant: communities</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-01164'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_210' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Hanningfield</span> moved Amendment No. 100:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-01165'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_211' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 18, line 18, at end insert&#x2014;
        <q>( ) Any payments made by the Secretary of State under subsection (1) must not be financed by monies recouped from debt free councils via capital receipts.</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-01166'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_212' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: At this point we move on to the position in Wales. This amendment aims to ensure the transparency of any grant paid to a best value community council under the terms of Clause 37 by the National Assembly for Wales by ensuring that it is scrutinised by Parliament. This is a similar issue to that raised by the previous amendment.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-01167'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_213' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Again, we welcome the Government's good intention to reward good performance in all kinds of councils in England and in Wales. We support awarding grants to enable councils to meet the requirements of best value status once it has been attained.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-01168'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_214' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        However, as we discussed under Amendment No. 99 in relation to parish councils in England, we would prefer all best value grants to be scrutinised by Parliament. If that cannot be done, let us introduce some form of process by which the award of grants is made more transparent. However, we also want to see how the Welsh Assembly may deal with the issue.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-01169'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_215' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        This amendment will ensure that grants paid under Clause 37 by the National Assembly for Wales are reported to Parliament in the appropriate manner. This will maintain the transparency and the credibility of such transactions and, as we discussed during the
        
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_93gc' title='Col. 93GC &mdash; HL Deb 10 June 2003 vol 649 c93GC' name='column_93gc' href='#column_93gc' rel='bookmark'>93GC</a>
        previous amendment, it will provide a clear incentive for those councils striving to improve their performance. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0649P0-01170'>
        <a name='S5LV0649P0_20030610_GCR_216'>  </a>
