          <p class='first-para'>
            I am sorry, but the noble Lord has not answered my point. We have just pointed out on the earlier amendment that the Government have no power to tell the Welsh Assembly to publish or make available a list, but here the Bill takes the power to tell the Assembly that it can change or vary a grant. That is the point I sought to make.</p><p>
            The noble Lord, Lord Rooker, said that we cannot tell the National Assembly for Wales to publish a list, but we can tell them to vary the grant. I find the whole thing inconsistent and I do think the Minister has responded to that.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0649P0-01186'>
